        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[arjuna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0930\u094d\u091c\u0941\u0928]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[vEdA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u0947\u0926\u093e\u0903]</span> the Vedas <span class='transliteration'>[traiguNya viShayA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0948\u0917\u0941\u0923\u094d\u092f \u0935\u093f\u0937\u092f\u093e\u0903]</span> deal with those who have the three qualities in abundance. <span class='transliteration'>[nistraiguNyO bhava]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0948\u0917\u0941\u0923\u094d\u092f\u094b \u092d\u0935]</span> Be a person who is not drowned by an excess of these three qualities. <span class='transliteration'>[nirdvandva:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u0926\u094d\u0935\u0928\u094d\u0926\u094d\u0935\u0903]</span> Be free from the dualities of the material world. <span class='transliteration'>[nitya sattvastha:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0924\u094d\u092f \u0938\u0924\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0935\u0938\u094d\u0925\u0903]</span> Be constantly situated in an abundance of the quality of sattva. <span class='transliteration'>[niryOgakShEma:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u092f\u094b\u0917\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0947\u092e\u0903]</span> Do not care about protecting what you have and don\u2019t bother to acquire what you don\u2019t. <span class='transliteration'>[AtmavAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> Know the nature of your Self.<br><span class='transliteration'>[vijAnata: brAhmaNasya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u091c\u093e\u0928\u0924\u0903 \u092c\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0939\u094d\u092e\u0923\u0938\u094d\u092f]</span> A man of wisdom seeking God <span class='transliteration'>[yAvAnartha: tAvAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u093e\u0935\u093e\u0928\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0903 \u0924\u093e\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> will find as much use <span class='transliteration'>[sarvEShu vEdEShu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0947\u0937\u0941 \u0935\u0947\u0926\u0947\u0937\u0941]</span> in all the Vedas, <span class='transliteration'>[yAvAn artha: tAvAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u093e\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0905\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0903 \u0924\u093e\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> as one will find use <span class='transliteration'>[udapAnE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0909\u0926\u092a\u093e\u0928\u0947]</span> in a lake, <span class='transliteration'>[sarvata: samplutOdakE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0924\u0903 \u0938\u092e\u094d\u092a\u094d\u0932\u0941\u0924\u094b\u0926\u0915\u0947]</span> that is full of water in every respect.",
