        "shloka": "yajnArthAt karmaNO_nyatra lOkO_yam karma bandhana: |<br>tadartham karma kauntEya mukta sanga: samAchara || 9 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[karmaNa:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u0923\u0903]</span> Other than actions <span class='transliteration'>[yajnArthAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0925\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> done for the purpose of worship, <span class='transliteration'>[anyatra]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u094d\u092f\u0924\u094d\u0930]</span> all other actions <span class='transliteration'>[karma bandhana:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e \u092c\u0928\u094d\u0927\u0928\u0903]</span> are limiting (binding) in nature <span class='transliteration'>[ayam lOka:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092f\u092e\u094d \u0932\u094b\u0915\u0903]</span> for the people of this world. <span class='transliteration'>[kauntEya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094c\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0947\u092f]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[samAchara]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u093e\u091a\u0930]</span> perform <span class='transliteration'>[karma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e]</span> actions <span class='transliteration'>[tadartham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0926\u0930\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d]</span> for the sake of worship, <span class='transliteration'>[mukta sanga:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0941\u0915\u094d\u0924 \u0938\u0919\u094d\u0917\u0903]</span> being free from all attachments and addictions.",
