        "shloka": "dEvAn bhAvayatAnEna tE dEvA bhAvayantu va: |<br>parasparam bhAvayanta: shrEya: param avApsyatha || 11 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[bhAvayata]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u093e\u0935\u092f\u0924]</span> By adoring <span class='transliteration'>[dEvAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0947\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> the gods <span class='transliteration'>[anEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u0947\u0928]</span> via these forms of worship, <span class='transliteration'>[tE dEvA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947 \u0926\u0947\u0935\u093e\u0903]</span> let those gods <span class='transliteration'>[va: bhAvayantu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u0903 \u092d\u093e\u0935\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0941]</span> nourish you. <span class='transliteration'>[parasparam bhAvayanta:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u0938\u094d\u092a\u0930\u092e\u094d \u092d\u093e\u0935\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0903]</span> By adoring each other, <span class='transliteration'>[avApsyatha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0935\u093e\u092a\u094d\u0938\u094d\u092f\u0925]</span> you will obtain <span class='transliteration'>[param shrEya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u092e\u094d \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0947\u092f\u0903]</span> ultimate superiority.",
