        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[yastu mAnava:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0941 \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0935\u0903]</span> The person who <span class='transliteration'>[Atmarati: Eva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0930\u0924\u093f\u0903 \u090f\u0935]</span> is always inclined towards the Self, <span class='transliteration'>[Atma tr`ptashcha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e \u0924\u0943\u092a\u094d\u0924\u0936\u094d\u091a]</span> satisfied in the Self alone, <span class='transliteration'>[Atmani Eva santuShTa:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0928\u093f \u090f\u0935 \u0938\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0941\u0937\u094d\u091f\u0903]</span> and who enjoys being in the Self alone - <span class='transliteration'>[tasya kAryam na vidyatE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092f \u0915\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d \u0928 \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u0924\u0947]</span> he is not bound to perform any actions.<br><span class='transliteration'>[tasya kr`tEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092f \u0915\u0943\u0924\u0947\u0928]</span> Activity <span class='transliteration'>[artha: naiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0903 \u0928\u0948\u0935]</span> does not fulfil his wish. <span class='transliteration'>[iha kashchana na]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0907\u0939 \u0915\u0936\u094d\u091a\u0928 \u0928]</span> there is no consequence over here, <span class='transliteration'>[akr`tEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0915\u0943\u0924\u0947\u0928]</span> if he does not perform something. <span class='transliteration'>[asya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u094d\u092f]</span> To him, <span class='transliteration'>[kashchit arthavyapAshraya: naiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d \u0905\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0935\u094d\u092f\u092a\u093e\u0936\u094d\u0930\u092f\u0903 \u0928\u0948\u0935]</span> benefit-driven relationships do not exist. <br><span class='transliteration'>[tasmAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> Hence, <span class='transliteration'>[satatam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0924\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> always <span class='transliteration'>[samAchara]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u093e\u091a\u0930]</span> perform <span class='transliteration'>[kAryam karma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e]</span> your activity, <span class='transliteration'>[asakta:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u0915\u094d\u0924\u0903]</span> without being driven by attachments or addictions. <span class='transliteration'>[Acharan hi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u091a\u0930\u0928\u094d \u0939\u093f]</span> Only by performing <span class='transliteration'>[karma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e]</span> actions <span class='transliteration'>[asakta:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u0915\u094d\u0924\u0903]</span> without being driven by attachments, <span class='transliteration'>[pUruSha:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0942\u0930\u0941\u0937\u0903]</span> a person <span class='transliteration'>[param ApnOti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u092e\u094d \u0906\u092a\u094d\u0928\u094b\u0924\u093f]</span> will attain the realization of the Self.",
