        "shloka": "Evam buddhE: param buddhvA samstabhyAtmAnam AtmanA |<br>jahi shatrum mahAbAhO kAmarUpam durAsadam || 43 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[mahAbAhO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0939\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0939\u094b]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[Evam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0935\u092e\u094d]</span> in this way, <span class='transliteration'>[buddhvA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u0941\u0926\u094d\u0927\u094d\u0935\u093e]</span> knowing <span class='transliteration'>[buddhE: param]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u0941\u0926\u094d\u0927\u0947\u0903 \u092a\u0930\u092e\u094d]</span> this to be even more powerful than the intellect, <span class='transliteration'>[samstabhya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u094d\u0938\u094d\u0924\u092d\u094d\u092f]</span> having supported <span class='transliteration'>[AtmAnam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> your mind <span class='transliteration'>[AtmanA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0928\u093e]</span> with intellect born out of your Self, <span class='transliteration'>[jahi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091c\u0939\u093f]</span> abandon <span class='transliteration'>[kAmarUpam shatrum]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093e\u092e\u0930\u0942\u092a\u092e\u094d \u0936\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0941\u092e\u094d]</span> this enemy called desire <span class='transliteration'>[durAsadam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0941\u0930\u093e\u0938\u0926\u092e\u094d]</span> which is, indeed, very difficult to destroy.",
