        "shloka": "Evam bahuvidhA yajnA vitatA brahmaNO mukhE |<br>karmajAn viddhi tAn sarvAn Evam jnAtvA vimOkShyasE || 32 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[Evam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0935\u092e\u094d]</span> In this way, <span class='transliteration'>[bahuvidhA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u0939\u0941\u0935\u093f\u0927\u093e\u0903]</span> many varieties of <span class='transliteration'>[yajnA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0903]</span> worship <span class='transliteration'>[vitatA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0924\u0924\u093e\u0903]</span> were elaborated <span class='transliteration'>[brahmaNO mukhE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u094d\u0930\u0939\u094d\u092e\u0923\u094b \u092e\u0941\u0916\u0947]</span> as ways in which we can realize the Self. <span class='transliteration'>[viddhi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093f]</span> Know <span class='transliteration'>[sarvAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> them all <span class='transliteration'>[karmajAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u091c\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> to be born out of activity. <span class='transliteration'>[Evam jnAtvA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0935\u092e\u094d \u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0924\u094d\u0935\u093e]</span> Knowing this, <span class='transliteration'>[vimOkShyasE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u092e\u094b\u0915\u094d\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0938\u0947]</span> you will attain Moksha.",
