        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[vibhu:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u092d\u0941\u0903]</span> The omnipresent Self <span class='transliteration'>[nAdattE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093e\u0926\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0947]</span> does not take up <span class='transliteration'>[kasyachit pApam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0938\u094d\u092f\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d \u092a\u093e\u092a\u092e\u094d]</span> anyone\u2019s sinful deeds. <span class='transliteration'>[na chaiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u091a\u0948\u0935]</span> Nor does it take up <span class='transliteration'>[sukr`tam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0941\u0915\u0943\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> any virtuous deeds. <span class='transliteration'>[jnAnam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> The inherent knowledge in the Self <span class='transliteration'>[Avr`tam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0935\u0943\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> is concealed <span class='transliteration'>[ajnAnEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0928\u0947\u0928]</span> by ignorance. <span class='transliteration'>[tEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947\u0928]</span> Due to this, <span class='transliteration'>[jantava:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091c\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0935\u0903]</span> the various beings <span class='transliteration'>[muhyanti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0941\u0939\u094d\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> are misled into believing that the body is their Self.",
