        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[Atmana:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0928\u0903]</span> The Self <span class='transliteration'>[yOgina:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u094b\u0917\u093f\u0928\u0903]</span> in a person who works purely as worship to the Lord, <span class='transliteration'>[yatachittasya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092f]</span> who controls his consciousness, <span class='transliteration'>[yOgam yunjata:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u094b\u0917\u092e\u094d \u092f\u0941\u0928\u094d\u091c\u0924\u0903]</span> who is dedicated and focused in his quest to realize the Self <span class='transliteration'>[sOpamA smr`tA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u094b\u092a\u092e\u093e \u0938\u094d\u092e\u0943\u0924\u093e]</span> is considered similar to <span class='transliteration'>[dIpa:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0940\u092a\u0903]</span> a flame <span class='transliteration'>[yathA nEngatE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0925\u093e \u0928\u0947\u0919\u094d\u0917\u0924\u0947]</span> that stays without shaking <span class='transliteration'>[nivAtastha:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0935\u093e\u0924\u0938\u094d\u0925\u0903]</span> in a place without winds.",
