        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[pravakShyE sangrahENa]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0935\u0915\u094d\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0947 \u0938\u0919\u094d\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939\u0947\u0923]</span> I will now summarize <span class='transliteration'>[tE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947]</span> to you <span class='transliteration'>[tat padam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u094d \u092a\u0926\u092e\u094d]</span> that position, <span class='transliteration'>[yat]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d]</span> which <span class='transliteration'>[vEdavida:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u0947\u0926\u0935\u093f\u0926\u0903]</span> the people who know the Vedas <span class='transliteration'>[akSharam vadanti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0930\u092e\u094d \u0935\u0926\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> call as 'the indestructible'; <span class='transliteration'>[yat]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d]</span> that place, which <span class='transliteration'>[yataya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u092f\u0903]</span> people who persevere <span class='transliteration'>[vItarAgA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u0940\u0924\u0930\u093e\u0917\u093e\u0903]</span> without being driven by desire <span class='transliteration'>[vishanti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0936\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> enter; <span class='transliteration'>[yat ichChantO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d \u0907\u091a\u094d\u091b\u0928\u094d\u0924\u094b]</span> yearning for which, <span class='transliteration'>[charanti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a\u0930\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> people practice <span class='transliteration'>[brahmacharyam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u094d\u0930\u0939\u094d\u092e\u091a\u0930\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> celibacy and study.",
