        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[pArtha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0925]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[kashchana]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0936\u094d\u091a\u0928]</span> any <span class='transliteration'>[jAnan yOgI]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091c\u093e\u0928\u0928\u094d \u092f\u094b\u0917\u0940]</span> devotee who practices yoga and knows <span class='transliteration'>[EtE sr'tI]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0924\u0947 \u0938\u0943\u0924\u0940]</span> these paths <span class='transliteration'>[na muhyati]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u092e\u0941\u0939\u094d\u092f\u0924\u093f]</span> will not get bewildered. <span class='transliteration'>[tasmAt arjuna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d \u0905\u0930\u094d\u091c\u0941\u0928]</span> Hence, Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[yOga yuktO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092f\u0941\u0915\u094d\u0924\u094b]</span> be with yoga <span class='transliteration'>[sarvEShu kAlEShu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0947\u0937\u0941 \u0915\u093e\u0932\u0947\u0937\u0941]</span> at all times.",
