        "shloka": "prakr'tim svAm avaShTabhya visr'jAmi puna: puna: |<br>bhUta grAmam imam kr'tsnam avasham prakr'tErvashAt || 8 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[visr'jAmi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0938\u0943\u091c\u093e\u092e\u093f]</span> I create <span class='transliteration'>[imam kr'tsnam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0907\u092e\u092e\u094d \u0915\u0943\u0924\u094d\u0938\u094d\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> this entire <span class='transliteration'>[bhUta grAmam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u0942\u0924 \u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e\u092e\u094d]</span> system of beings <span class='transliteration'>[puna: puna:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0941\u0928\u0903 \u092a\u0941\u0928\u0903]</span> again and again, <span class='transliteration'>[prakr'tim svam avaShTabhya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u0943\u0924\u093f\u092e\u094d \u0938\u094d\u0935\u092e\u094d \u0905\u0935\u0937\u094d\u091f\u092d\u094d\u092f]</span> while keeping My material nature as the basis. <span class='transliteration'>[prakr'tErvashAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u0943\u0924\u0947\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0936\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> Under the influence of the material world, <span class='transliteration'>[avasham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0935\u0936\u092e\u094d]</span> they are not free.",
