        "shloka": "kirITinam gadinam chakriNam chatEjOrAshim sarvatO dIptimantam |<br>parshyAmi tvAm durnirIkSham samantAtdIptAnalArka dyutim apramEyam || 17 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[pashyAmi tvAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0936\u094d\u092f\u093e\u092e\u093f \u0924\u094d\u0935\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> I see you <span class='transliteration'>[kirITinam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093f\u0930\u0940\u091f\u093f\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> crowned, <span class='transliteration'>[gadinam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0926\u093f\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> bearing a mace <span class='transliteration'>[chakriNam cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a\u0915\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0923\u092e\u094d \u091a]</span> and a disc. <span class='transliteration'>[samantAt durnirIkSham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0924\u094d \u0926\u0941\u0930\u094d\u0928\u093f\u0930\u0940\u0915\u094d\u0937\u092e\u094d]</span> You are impossible to see completely. <span class='transliteration'>[tEjOrAshim]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947\u091c\u094b\u0930\u093e\u0936\u093f\u092e\u094d]</span> You are abundant energy. <span class='transliteration'>[sarvata: dIptimantam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0924\u0903 \u0926\u0940\u092a\u094d\u0924\u093f\u092e\u0928\u094d\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> You are brilliant in every direction. <span class='transliteration'>[dIptAnalArka dyutim]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0940\u092a\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0928\u0932\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0915 \u0926\u094d\u092f\u0941\u0924\u093f\u092e\u094d]</span> You have the light of a blazing sun. <span class='transliteration'>[apramEyam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092a\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0947\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> You are beyond quantification.",
