      "content": {
        "devanagri": "\u0915\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d \u091a \u0924\u0947 \u0928 \u0928\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0928\u094d \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0928\u094d\u0917\u0930\u0940\u092f\u0938\u0947 \u092c\u094d\u0930\u0939\u094d\u092e\u0923\u094b\u093d\u092a\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0926\u093f\u0915\u0930\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0947 \u0964",
        "shloka": "kasmAt cha tE na namEran mahAtmangarIyasE brahmaNO_pyAdikartrE |",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[mahAtman]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0939\u093e\u0924\u094d\u092e\u0928\u094d]</span> Lord, <span class='transliteration'>[kasmAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> why <span class='transliteration'>[na namEran]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u0928\u092e\u0947\u0930\u0928\u094d]</span> would anyone not bow <span class='transliteration'>[tE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947]</span> to You? <span class='transliteration'>[AdikartrE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0926\u093f\u0915\u0930\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0947]</span> You are the origin <span class='transliteration'>[brahmaNa: api]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u094d\u0930\u0939\u094d\u092e\u0923\u0903 \u0905\u092a\u093f]</span> of Brahma himself, the principal engineer of this universe, <span class='transliteration'>[garIyasE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0930\u0940\u092f\u0938\u0947]</span> towering over everything else.",
        "insights": [
          [
            "At times we experience the universe as being terrible, due to the influence of past deeds.",
            "Lord, why would anyone not bow to You, the origin of Brahma himself, the principal engineer of the universe, when You tower over everything else?"
          ]
        ]
      }
