        "devanagri": "\u0905\u0928\u0928\u094d\u0924 \u0935\u0940\u0930\u094d\u092f\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0924 \u0935\u093f\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0935\u092e\u094d\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u092e\u094d \u0938\u092e\u093e\u092a\u094d\u0928\u094b\u0937\u093f \u0924\u0924\u094b\u093d\u0938\u093f \u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0903 \u0965 \u096a\u0966 \u0965",
        "shloka": "ananta vIryAmita vikramastvamsarvam samApnOShi tatO_si sarva: || 40 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[tvam ananta vIrya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u094d\u0935\u092e\u094d \u0905\u0928\u0928\u094d\u0924 \u0935\u0940\u0930\u094d\u092f]</span> You have unlimited valor <span class='transliteration'>[amita vikrama:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092e\u093f\u0924 \u0935\u093f\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0903]</span> and infinite might. <span class='transliteration'>[samApnOShi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u093e\u092a\u094d\u0928\u094b\u0937\u093f]</span> You pervade as the Self in everything, <span class='transliteration'>[tata:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u0903]</span> hence <span class='transliteration'>[sarva: asi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0903 \u0905\u0938\u093f]</span> You are everything.",
        "insights": [
          [
            "At times we experience the universe as being terrible, due to the influence of past deeds.",
            "\u2018Valor\u2019 is the ability to perform great deeds while being unaffected as a result of doing them. <br>With unlimited valor, You have infinite might and are present as the Self in everything. Hence You are everything. Since You pervade all conscious and non-conscious things as their Self, they are present as Your body. <br>In this way, You alone are addressed by all words. <br>It was mentioned in Chap.11#37 \u2018You are the imperishable, You are the outcome and the origin\u2019 and in Chap.10#39 \u2018You are the wind, restraint, fire, the atmosphere, the ocean, the moon, the leader of people, and their great-grandfather - their origin\u2019. You have equivalence to everything - that's because You are present as the Self in everything. This is described appropriately in Chap.11#38 \u2018You are the One with an unending form; the universe is pervaded by You\u2019."
          ]
        ]
