        "shloka": "kirITinam gadinam chakra hastamichChAmi tvAm draShTum aham tathaiva |<br>tEnaiva rUpENa chaturbhujEnasahasra bAhO bhava vishva mUrtE || 46 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[aham draShTum ichChAmi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0939\u092e\u094d \u0926\u094d\u0930\u0937\u094d\u091f\u0941\u092e\u094d \u0907\u091a\u094d\u091b\u093e\u092e\u093f]</span> I desire to see You <span class='transliteration'>[tathaiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0925\u0948\u0935]</span> in the same way - <span class='transliteration'>[kirItinam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093f\u0930\u0940\u0924\u093f\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> with a crown, <span class='transliteration'>[gadinam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0926\u093f\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> a mace, <span class='transliteration'>[chakra hastam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a\u0915\u094d\u0930 \u0939\u0938\u094d\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> with the disc in Your hand, <span class='transliteration'>[sahasra bAhO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0939\u0938\u094d\u0930 \u092c\u093e\u0939\u094b]</span> O One with a thousand arms. <span class='transliteration'>[vishva mUrtE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935 \u092e\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0924\u0947]</span> O Lord who has the universe as the body, <span class='transliteration'>[bhava]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u0935]</span> be <span class='transliteration'>[tEnaiva rUpENa]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0947\u0928\u0948\u0935 \u0930\u0942\u092a\u0947\u0923]</span> with that form, <span class='transliteration'>[chaturbhujEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a\u0924\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092d\u0941\u091c\u0947\u0928]</span> which has four arms ",
