        "shloka": "shrI bhagavAn uvAcha -<br>idam sharIram kauntEya kShEtram ityabhidhIyatE |<br>Etat yO vEtti tam prAhu: kShEtrajna iti tadvida: || 1 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[shrI bhagavAn uvAcha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u092d\u0917\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0909\u0935\u093e\u091a]</span> Lord Krishna said- <span class='transliteration'>[kauntEya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094c\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0947\u092f]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[idam sharIram]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0907\u0926\u092e\u094d \u0936\u0930\u0940\u0930\u092e\u094d]</span> this body <span class='transliteration'>[abhidhIyatE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092d\u093f\u0927\u0940\u092f\u0924\u0947]</span> is said to be <span class='transliteration'>[kShEtram]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0947\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092e\u094d]</span> the field of action. <span class='transliteration'>[tadvida:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0926\u094d\u0935\u093f\u0926\u0903]</span> People who know it <span class='transliteration'>[prAhu:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0939\u0941\u0903]</span> call <span class='transliteration'>[yO vEtti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u094b \u0935\u0947\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> the one who is aware of <span class='transliteration'>[Etat]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0924\u0924\u094d]</span> this body <span class='transliteration'>[kShEtrajna iti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0947\u0924\u094d\u0930\u091c\u094d\u091e \u0907\u0924\u093f]</span> as the knower of the field.",
