        "shloka": "prakr'tim puruSham chaiva viddhi anAdi ubhau api |<br>vikArAn cha guNAn chaiva viddhi prakr'ti sambhavAn || 19 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[viddhi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093f]</span> Know that <span class='transliteration'>[ubhau]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0909\u092d\u094c]</span> both <span class='transliteration'>[prakr'tim]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u0943\u0924\u093f\u092e\u094d]</span> the material environment <span class='transliteration'>[puruSham cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0937\u092e\u094d \u091a]</span> and the Self <span class='transliteration'>[anAdi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u093e\u0926\u093f]</span> are without a beginning <span class='transliteration'>[api]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092a\u093f]</span> too. <span class='transliteration'>[viddhi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093f]</span> Know that <span class='transliteration'>[vikArAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0915\u093e\u0930\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> the changes we undergo <span class='transliteration'>[guNAn cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0941\u0923\u093e\u0928\u094d \u091a]</span> and our qualities <span class='transliteration'>[prakr'ti sambhavAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0915\u0943\u0924\u093f \u0938\u092e\u094d\u092d\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> are born out of the material environment.",
