        "shloka": "tamastu ajnAnajam viddhi mOhanam sarva dEhinAm |<br>pramAda Alasya nidrAbhi: tat nibadhnAti bhArata || 8 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[bhArata]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u093e\u0930\u0924]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[viddhi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093f]</span> know <span class='transliteration'>[tama: tu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u092e\u0903 \u0924\u0941]</span> tamas to be a quality that <span class='transliteration'>[ajnAnajam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u091c\u094d\u091e\u093e\u0928\u091c\u092e\u094d]</span> gives rise to ignorance <span class='transliteration'>[mOhanam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u094b\u0939\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> and delusion <span class='transliteration'>[sarva dEhinAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935 \u0926\u0947\u0939\u093f\u0928\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> in every Self that owns a body. <span class='transliteration'>[tat nibadhnAti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u094d \u0928\u093f\u092c\u0927\u094d\u0928\u093e\u0924\u093f]</span> It binds the Self <span class='transliteration'>[pramAda]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u092e\u093e\u0926]</span> with carelessness, <span class='transliteration'>[Alasya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0932\u0938\u094d\u092f]</span> lethargy <span class='transliteration'>[nidrAbhi:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092d\u093f\u0903]</span> and drowsiness.",
