        "devanagri": "\u0905\u0936\u094d\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d \u090f\u0928\u092e\u094d \u0938\u0935\u093f\u0930\u0942\u0922\u092e\u0942\u0932\u092e\u094d\u0905\u0938\u0919\u094d\u0917 \u0936\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0923 \u0926\u0943\u0922\u0947\u0928 \u091b\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0935\u093e \u0965 \u0969 \u0965<br>\u0924\u0924\u0903 \u092a\u0926\u092e\u094d \u0924\u0924\u094d \u092a\u0930\u093f\u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0917\u093f\u0924\u0935\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d\u092f\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093f\u0928\u094d \u0917\u0924\u093e \u0928 \u0928\u093f\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0924\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f \u092d\u0942\u092f\u0903 \u0964",
        "shloka": "ashvattham Enam savirUDhamUlamasanga shastrENa dr'DhEna ChitvA || 3 ||<br>tata: padam tat parimArgitavyamyasmin gatA na nivartanti bhUya: |",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[ChitvA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091b\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0935\u093e]</span> Having cut off <span class='transliteration'>[Enam ashvattham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u090f\u0928\u092e\u094d \u0905\u0936\u094d\u0935\u0924\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d]</span> this pepal tree <span class='transliteration'>[savirUDhamUlam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0935\u093f\u0930\u0942\u0922\u092e\u0942\u0932\u092e\u094d]</span> with its overgrown roots <span class='transliteration'>[asanga shastrENa]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u0919\u094d\u0917 \u0936\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0923]</span> using the weapon of decoupling <span class='transliteration'>[dr'DhEna]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0943\u0922\u0947\u0928]</span> and strength, <span class='transliteration'>[tata: tat padam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u0903 \u0924\u0924\u094d \u092a\u0926\u092e\u094d]</span> that goal <span class='transliteration'>[parimArgitavyam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u093f\u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0917\u093f\u0924\u0935\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> is to be sought - <span class='transliteration'>[yasmin gatA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093f\u0928\u094d \u0917\u0924\u093e\u0903]</span> the state from which <span class='transliteration'>[na nivartanti bhUya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u0928\u093f\u0935\u0930\u094d\u0924\u0928\u094d\u0924\u093f \u092d\u0942\u092f\u0903]</span> people do not return anymore.",
        "insights": [
          [
            ".",
            "This pepal tree, which was described before, is famous for its numerous well-grown roots and shoots. By knowing it, a person uses the \u2018weapon of decoupling\u2019 to cut free of their grip. \u2018Decoupling\u2019 is to leave attachment to experiences that are loaded with material qualities. <br>He well and truly cuts free with firm perseverance.<br>Then, with the Self being free from the stimuli of the environment, he must seek that permanent goal, entering which people don't return anymore.<br>How can we get away from our in-built attachment to experience materials and their qualities? These attachments have been with us since beginning-less time. The misconception that the body is the Self gives rise to such attachments. How do we rid ourselves of this misconception? The Lord explains next -"
          ]
        ]
