        "shloka": "dvA bhUtasargau lOkE_smin daiva asura Eva cha |<br>daivO vistarasha: prOkta: Asuram pArtha mE shr'Nu || 6 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[asmin lOkE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093f\u0928\u094d \u0932\u094b\u0915\u0947]</span> In this world, <span class='transliteration'>[dvA bhUtasargau]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u094d\u0935\u093e \u092d\u0942\u0924\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0917\u094c]</span> two types of beings take form - <span class='transliteration'>[daiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0948\u0935]</span> those who intend to comply to My instructions <span class='transliteration'>[asura]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u0941\u0930]</span> and those who don't. <span class='transliteration'>[daivO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0948\u0935\u094b]</span> The property of compliance <span class='transliteration'>[prokta:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0915\u094d\u0924\u0903]</span> was described <span class='transliteration'>[vistarasha:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0924\u0930\u0936\u0903]</span> in an elaborate manner. <span class='transliteration'>[pArtha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0925]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[shr'Nu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u0943\u0923\u0941]</span> listen <span class='transliteration'>[Asuram]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0938\u0941\u0930\u092e\u094d]</span> to the property of non-compliance <span class='transliteration'>[mE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0947]</span> from Me.",
