        "shloka": "ADhyO_bhijanavAn asmi kO_nyO_sti sadr'shO mayA |<br>yakShyE dAsyAmi mOdiShyE iti ajnAna vimOhitA: || 15 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[asmi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093f]</span> 'I am <span class='transliteration'>[ADhya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0922\u094d\u092f\u0903]</span> rich, <span class='transliteration'>[abhijanavAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092d\u093f\u091c\u0928\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> born in a superior race. <span class='transliteration'>[ka: anya: asti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0903 \u0905\u0928\u094d\u092f\u0903 \u0905\u0938\u094d\u0924\u093f]</span> Who else <span class='transliteration'>[sadr'sha:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0926\u0943\u0936\u0903]</span> compares to <span class='transliteration'>[mayA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u092f\u093e]</span> me? <span class='transliteration'>[yakShyE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0947]</span> I work hard <span class='transliteration'>[dAsyAmi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u093e\u0938\u094d\u092f\u093e\u092e\u093f]</span> and donate wealth, <span class='transliteration'>[mOdiShyE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u094b\u0926\u093f\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0947]</span> I enjoy it. <span class='transliteration'>[anjAna vimOhitA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u094d\u091c\u093e\u0928 \u0935\u093f\u092e\u094b\u0939\u093f\u0924\u093e\u0903]</span> These people are deluded by ignorance' <span class='transliteration'>[iti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0907\u0924\u093f]</span> - so they believe.",
