        "devanagri": "\u0905\u0936\u093e\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0935\u093f\u0939\u093f\u0924\u092e\u094d \u0918\u094b\u0930\u092e\u094d \u0924\u092a\u094d\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0947 \u092f\u0947 \u0924\u092a\u094b \u091c\u0928\u093e\u0903 \u0964<br>\u0926\u092e\u094d\u092d\u093e\u0939\u0902\u0915\u093e\u0930 \u0938\u092e\u094d\u092f\u0941\u0915\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0903 \u0915\u093e\u092e \u0930\u093e\u0917 \u092c\u0932\u093e\u0928\u094d\u0935\u093f\u0924\u093e\u0903 \u0965 \u096b \u0965<br>\u0915\u0930\u094d\u0936\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0903 \u0936\u0930\u0940\u0930\u0938\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d \u092d\u0942\u0924\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e\u092e\u094d \u0905\u091a\u0947\u0924\u0938\u0903 \u0964<br>\u092e\u093e\u092e\u094d \u091a\u0948\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0903 \u0936\u0930\u0940\u0930\u0938\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d \u0924\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u0941\u0930 \u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u092f\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0965 \u096c \u0965",
        "shloka": "ashAstravihitam ghOram tapyantE yE tapO janA: |<br>dambhAhaMkAra samyuktA: kAma rAga balAnvitA: || 5 ||<br>karshayanta: sharIrastham bhUtagrAmam achEtasa: |<br>mAm chaivAnta: sharIrastham tAn vidyAsura nishchayAn || 6 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[yE janA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0947 \u091c\u0928\u093e\u0903]</span> People who <span class='transliteration'>[samyuktA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u092e\u094d\u092f\u0941\u0915\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0903]</span> are associated with <span class='transliteration'>[dambha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u092e\u094d\u092d]</span> hypocrisy <span class='transliteration'>[ahaMkAra]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0939\u0902\u0915\u093e\u0930]</span> and arrogance <span class='transliteration'>[balAnvitA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u0932\u093e\u0928\u094d\u0935\u093f\u0924\u093e\u0903]</span> find their strength <span class='transliteration'>[rAga]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0930\u093e\u0917]</span> in desire <span class='transliteration'>[kAma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093e\u092e]</span> and pleasure. <span class='transliteration'>[tapyantE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u092a\u094d\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0947]</span> They torment themselves <span class='transliteration'>[ghOram tapa:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0918\u094b\u0930\u092e\u094d \u0924\u092a\u0903]</span> with awful struggle, <span class='transliteration'>[ashAstravihitam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0936\u093e\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0935\u093f\u0939\u093f\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> going against My instructions in the scriptures.<br><span class='transliteration'>[karshayanta:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u0936\u092f\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0903]</span> They attenuate <span class='transliteration'>[bhUtagrAmam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u0942\u0924\u0917\u094d\u0930\u093e\u092e\u092e\u094d]</span> the colony of elements <span class='transliteration'>[sharIrastham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u0930\u0940\u0930\u0938\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d]</span> present as the body <span class='transliteration'>[chaiva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a\u0948\u0935]</span> along with <span class='transliteration'>[mAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> Me, <span class='transliteration'>[anta: sharIrastham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0903 \u0936\u0930\u0940\u0930\u0938\u094d\u0925\u092e\u094d]</span> present as the core of the body. <span class='transliteration'>[achEtasa:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u091a\u0947\u0924\u0938\u0903]</span> They are lifeless. <span class='transliteration'>[tAn viddhi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093f]</span> Know them <span class='transliteration'>[Asura nishchayAn]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0938\u0941\u0930 \u0928\u093f\u0936\u094d\u091a\u092f\u093e\u0928\u094d]</span> as people who have resolved to disregard My instructions.",
        "insights": [
          [
            "Given an outlook, we can choose to live in reality or live in vain.",
            "The statement 'People torment themselves with awful struggle, going against my instructions in the scriptures' is illustrative - any struggle that goes against My instruction is awful, even when it involves impressive rituals such as charity and sacrifice. Such an activity has hypocrisy and arrogance built-in, finding strength in desire and pleasure.<br>These activities attenuate the specialty of the body - they diminish the body, not recognizing that it's a wonderful colony of the five elements - solids, liquids, energy, gasses and space. They also diminish the Self, a part of Me present as the core of the body. <br>Know that people who struggle this way have resolved to disregard My instructions. They are the very people who go against My instructions. By doing so, they don't get to touch even a little joy. Instead, they fall into the company of the vain and wasted, as said before in Chap.16#16: 'Indulging in their desires and experiences, they fall into foul torment'In addition to activities to achieve The Lord, the scriptures describe activities related to our environment. Next, The Lord goes on to distinguish activities that relate to our environment. These activities are characterized by the three qualities.<br>Food is the source of these activities - hence, He first describes the three types of food that nourish the three qualities. As said in [ChAMdOgya, 6-5, 4] - 'Son, the mind is defined by the food we eat' and in [ChAMdOgya, 7-26-2] - 'The quality of sattva gets pure when our food is free of impurities'. "
          ]
        ]
