        "shloka": "yAtayAmam gatarasam pUti paryuShitam cha yat |<br>uchChiShTam api chAmEdhyam bhOjanam tAmasa priyam || 10 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[tAmasa priyam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u093e\u092e\u0938 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> Creatures that are in tamas <span class='transliteration'>[yat bhOjanam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d \u092d\u094b\u091c\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> like to eat food that is <span class='transliteration'>[yAtayAmam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u093e\u0924\u092f\u093e\u092e\u092e\u094d]</span> aged, <span class='transliteration'>[gatarasam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0924\u0930\u0938\u092e\u094d]</span> having lost its natural flavor, <span class='transliteration'>[pUti]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0942\u0924\u093f]</span> foul-smelling, <span class='transliteration'>[paryuShitam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u094d\u092f\u0941\u0937\u093f\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> stale, <span class='transliteration'>[uchChiShTam api]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0909\u091a\u094d\u091b\u093f\u0937\u094d\u091f\u092e\u094d \u0905\u092a\u093f]</span> even left-over fragments <span class='transliteration'>[amEdhyam cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092e\u0947\u0927\u094d\u092f\u092e\u094d \u091a]</span> and other dirty things.",
