        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[shrI bhagavAn uvAcha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u092d\u0917\u0935\u093e\u0928\u094d \u0909\u0935\u093e\u091a]</span> The Lord said - <span class='transliteration'>[kavaya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0935\u092f\u0903]</span> The wise <span class='transliteration'>[vidu:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0926\u0941\u0903]</span> know that <span class='transliteration'>[saMnyAsam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0902\u0928\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u092e\u094d]</span> renunciation <span class='transliteration'>[nyAsam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938\u092e\u094d]</span> is to leave <span class='transliteration'>[kAmyAnAm karmaNAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u093e\u092e\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0928\u093e\u092e\u094d \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u0923\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> actions that come from desire. <span class='transliteration'>[vichakShaNA:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u091a\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923\u093e\u0903]</span> Those who are experienced <span class='transliteration'>[prAhu:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0939\u0941\u0903]</span> say that <span class='transliteration'>[tyAgam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0917\u092e\u094d]</span> 'letting go' <span class='transliteration'>[phala tyAgam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092b\u0932 \u0924\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0917\u092e\u094d]</span> is about giving up expectation <span class='transliteration'>[sarva karma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935 \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e]</span> in all actions.",
