        "shloka": "anubandham kShayam hiMsAm anavEkShya cha pauruSham |<br>mOhAt ArabhyatE karma yat tat tAmasam uchyatE || 25 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[yat karma]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e]</span> Work that is <span class='transliteration'>[ArabhyatE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0906\u0930\u092d\u094d\u092f\u0924\u0947]</span> started <span class='transliteration'>[mOhAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u094b\u0939\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> out of misconception, <span class='transliteration'>[anavEkShya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u0935\u0947\u0915\u094d\u0937\u094d\u092f]</span> without considering <span class='transliteration'>[anubandham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0928\u0941\u092c\u0928\u094d\u0927\u092e\u094d]</span> the bondage it brings, <span class='transliteration'>[kShayam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094d\u0937\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> the associated expense, <span class='transliteration'>[hiMsAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0939\u093f\u0902\u0938\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> the distress <span class='transliteration'>[cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a]</span> and <span class='transliteration'>[pauruSham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094c\u0930\u0941\u0937\u092e\u094d]</span> our capability <span class='transliteration'>[tat]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u094d]</span> - that work <span class='transliteration'>[uchyatE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0909\u091a\u094d\u092f\u0924\u0947]</span> is said <span class='transliteration'>[tAmasam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u093e\u092e\u0938\u092e\u094d]</span> to be in the quality of tamas.",
