        "shloka": "yayA svapnam bhayam shOkam viShAdam madam Eva cha |<br>na vimunchati durmEdhA dhr'ti: sA pArtha tAmasI || 35 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[pArtha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u0925]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[yayA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u092f\u093e]</span>  the resolve by which <span class='transliteration'>[durmEdhA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0926\u0941\u0930\u094d\u092e\u0947\u0927\u093e]</span> an ignorant person <span class='transliteration'>[na vimunchati]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u0935\u093f\u092e\u0941\u0928\u094d\u091a\u0924\u093f]</span> doesn't give up <span class='transliteration'>[svapnam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u094d\u0935\u092a\u094d\u0928\u092e\u094d]</span> drowsiness, <span class='transliteration'>[bhayam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u092f\u092e\u094d]</span> fear, <span class='transliteration'>[shOkam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u094b\u0915\u092e\u094d]</span> misery, <span class='transliteration'>[viShAdam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0937\u093e\u0926\u092e\u094d]</span> dejection <span class='transliteration'>[cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a]</span> and <span class='transliteration'>[madam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0926\u092e\u094d]</span> intoxication <span class='transliteration'>[sA dhr'ti:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u093e \u0927\u0943\u0924\u093f\u0903]</span> - such resolve is <span class='transliteration'>[tAmasI]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u093e\u092e\u0938\u0940]</span> in tamas.",
