        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[yattat]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092f\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0924\u094d]</span> The happiness that <span class='transliteration'>[amr'tOpamam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u092e\u0943\u0924\u094b\u092a\u092e\u092e\u094d]</span> seems like bliss <span class='transliteration'>[agrE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0905\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947]</span> at first, <span class='transliteration'>[saMyOgAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u0902\u092f\u094b\u0917\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> bringing together <span class='transliteration'>[viShaya indriya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0937\u092f \u0907\u0928\u094d\u0926\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f]</span> our organs and their subjects, <span class='transliteration'>[pariNAmE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u093f\u0923\u093e\u092e\u0947]</span> ripens to become <span class='transliteration'>[viSham iva]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0937\u092e\u094d \u0907\u0935]</span> like poison <span class='transliteration'>[tat sukham]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0924\u094d \u0938\u0941\u0916\u092e\u094d]</span> - such happiness <span class='transliteration'>[smr'tam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u094d\u092e\u0943\u0924\u092e\u094d]</span> is known to be <span class='transliteration'>[rAjasam]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0930\u093e\u091c\u0938\u092e\u094d]</span> in rajas.",
