        "shloka": "brAhmaNa kShatriya vishAm shUdrANAm cha parantapa |<br>karmANi pravibhaktAni svabhAva prabhavai: guNai: || 41 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[parantapa]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u0930\u0928\u094d\u0924\u092a]</span> Arjuna, <span class='transliteration'>[karmANi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0923\u093f]</span> the activities <span class='transliteration'>[brAhmaNa]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092c\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0939\u094d\u092e\u0923]</span> of philosophers, <span class='transliteration'>[kShatriya]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f]</span> administrators, <span class='transliteration'>[vishAm]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0935\u093f\u0936\u093e\u092e\u094d]</span> traders, <span class='transliteration'>[cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a]</span> and <span class='transliteration'>[shUdra]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0936\u0942\u0926\u094d\u0930]</span> assistants <span class='transliteration'>[pravibhaktAni]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0935\u093f\u092d\u0915\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0928\u093f]</span> are classified <span class='transliteration'>[guNai:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0917\u0941\u0923\u0948\u0903]</span> as per the qualities <span class='transliteration'>[svabhAva prabhavai:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0938\u094d\u0935\u092d\u093e\u0935 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u092d\u0935\u0948\u0903]</span> that come from their inherent nature.",
