      "type": "text",
      "content": {
        "devanagri": "\u0928 \u091a \u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d \u092e\u0928\u0941\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0947\u0937\u0941 \u0915\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0928\u094d \u092e\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0915\u0943\u0924\u094d\u0924\u092e\u0903 \u0964<br>\u092d\u0935\u093f\u0924\u093e \u0928 \u091a \u092e\u0947 \u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d \u0905\u0928\u094d\u092f\u0903 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0924\u0930\u094b \u092d\u0941\u0935\u093f \u0965 \u096c\u096f \u0965",
        "shloka": "na cha tasmAt manuShyEShu kashchin mE priyakr'ttama: |<br>bhavitA na cha mE tasmAt anya: priyatarO bhuvi || 69 ||",
        "translation": "<span class='transliteration'>[cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a]</span> Moreover, <span class='transliteration'>[na kashchit]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u0915\u0936\u094d\u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d]</span> there is nobody <span class='transliteration'>[manuShyEShu]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0928\u0941\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0947\u0937\u0941]</span> among humans <span class='transliteration'>[priyakr'ttama:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0915\u0943\u0924\u094d\u0924\u092e\u0903]</span> who has done something more likeable <span class='transliteration'>[mE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0947]</span> for Me <span class='transliteration'>[tasmAt]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d]</span> than such a person. <span class='transliteration'>[cha]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u091a]</span> Further, <span class='transliteration'>[na bhavitA]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0928 \u092d\u0935\u093f\u0924\u093e]</span> there isn't going to be <span class='transliteration'>[tasmAt anya:]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u0924\u0938\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0924\u094d \u0905\u0928\u094d\u092f\u0903]</span> anyone else <span class='transliteration'>[priyatarO]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0924\u0930\u094b]</span> who is dearer <span class='transliteration'>[mE]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092e\u0947]</span> to Me <span class='transliteration'>[bhuvi]</span><span class='sanskrit'>[\u092d\u0941\u0935\u093f]</span> on earth.",
        "insights": [
          [
            "Share it with others who adore the Lord.",
            "Up until now, there hasn't been any other human who has done something dearer for My sake. There isn't going to be anyone else who is dearer to Me either. <br>Those who are unfit to receive this knowledge were described before describing those who deserve it. Revealing this to the unfit is less welcome than missing its revelation to a deserving person.<br>In the scriptures, usually the deserving characteristics are mentioned. It's implied that those who don\u2019t have such characteristics don't deserve it. However, here the undeserving case is listed first, indicating that the instruction to avoid narrating the knowledge to them takes precedence."
          ]
        ]
      }
